I"<h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
<ul>
  <li>You can emulate the example custom menu for the custom Menu portion of the assignment.</li>
  <li>onDraw() should draw the shapes for each menu</li>
  <li>When dragging (choosing within the menu), updateModel is important…</li>
  <li>For the Pie Menu…
    <ul>
      <li>Consider <strong>setting your View’s X/Y</strong> so that when you draw from the topleft corner, it draws the full circle
while the user’s click is located at the center of the circle.</li>
      <li>The angle system for Android</li>
      <li><strong>Text orientation of your pie menu does not have to match the video</strong> or even be centered. It just needs to fit within its slice and be inside the outermost black circle.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
